To compile libdvdnav for Windows or Mac OS X follow the steps below, note that
for Linux the libdvdnav4-dev package should be installed instead.

Mac OS X:
- Make sure XCode is installed and start a terminal.

- Extract the libdvdread sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Configure libdvdread using:
  ./configure2 --enable-static --disable-shared
  Ignore the error "./configure2: line 95: cd: /usr/local/: No such file or directory"

- Run make and copy the obj/libdvdread.a file to ext/dvdnav/bin.macx.

- Extract the libdvdnav sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- In the libdvdnav source tree; open the "configure2" file and comment out lines 106-114.

- Configure libdvdnav using:
  ./configure2 --enable-static --disable-shared --disable-debug --extra-cflags="-I../../libdvdread-4.2.0/src/"
  Ignore the error "./configure2: line 100: cd: /usr/local/: No such file or directory"

- Run make and copy obj/libdvdnav.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.macx.

Windows:
- Make sure MinGW and MSYS are installed and start a MinGW bash shell.

- Extract the dlfcn sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Configure dlfcn using:
  ./configure --enable-static
  Ignore the error "./configure: line 119: test: too many arguments"

- Run mingw32-make and copy libdl.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.win32.

- Extract the libdvdread sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Configure libdvdread using:
  ./configure2 --enable-static --disable-shared --disable-debug --extra-cflags="-I../../dlfcn-win32-r19/"
  Ignore the error "./configure2: line 95: cd: /usr/local/: No such file or directory"

- Run mingw32-make and copy obj/libdvdread.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.win32.

- Extract the libdvdnav sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- In the libdvdnav source tree; open the "configure2" file and comment out lines 106-114.
 
- Configure libdvdnav using:
  ./configure2 --enable-static --disable-shared --disable-debug --extra-cflags="-I../../libdvdread-4.2.0/src/"
  Ignore the error "./configure2: line 100: cd: /usr/local/: No such file or directory"

- Run mingw32-make and copy obj/libdvdnav.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.win32.
